{"type":"text","timestamp":1777995457025,"sessionID":"ses_207374345ffeChGcsvBFjHYxka","part":{"id":"prt_df8c9748c0011WmN1INREEkFNz","messageID":"msg_df8c911b7001Cp2AexmDWitLY0","sessionID":"ses_207374345ffeChGcsvBFjHYxka","type":"text","text":"## Routing Trace for sk-doc\n\n### 1. Intent Selected\n\n**OPTIMIZATION** — score 6.0 (two keyword matches: `\"optimize\"` ×3 + `\"llms.txt\"` ×3). No other intent scores above 0; the router returns `[\"OPTIMIZATION\"]` alone.\n\n### 2. CONDITIONAL-Loaded Resources\n\nPer `RESOURCE_MAP[\"OPTIMIZATION\"]`:\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `references/global/optimization.md` | Prose compression rules, deduplication patterns, token-budget enforcement, AI-context tuning |\n| `assets/documentation/llmstxt_templates.md` | Template and generation guidance for `llms.txt` (LLM discovery summary) |\n\n`references/global/quick_reference.md` is ALWAYS loaded regardless of intent.\n\n### 3. Response Shape\n\nThe sk-doc response would return:\n1. **Structure extract** — parsed H1/H2 skeleton, detected SKILL.md document type, current line/token counts\n2. **DQI quality scores** — AI-friendliness, conciseness, and frontmatter completeness with flagged violations\n3. **Optimization prescriptions** — a prioritized list of compressible sections (duplicate resource-domain prose vs RESOURCE_MAP, verbose workflows, redundant cross-references), each with a prose-compression directive and estimated token savings\n4. **LLMs.txt scaffold** — a generated `llms.txt` block following the `llmstxt_templates.md` pattern (skill name, one-line description, key trigger phrases, primary resource paths), ready to place alongside the skill for external AI discovery","time":{"start":1777995445388,"end":1777995457024}}}
